{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":236773,"duration_api_ms":235634,"num_turns":3,"result":"Here's a summary of what the analysis found:\n\n## `test-repos/` — ultrainit Reference Output for open-webui\n\nThis directory contains a **complete, production-grade `.claude/` configuration** generated by ultrainit for [open-webui](https://github.com/open-webui/open-webui), a full-stack self-hosted AI chat platform. It's used as both a reference example and integration validation fixture.\n\n### What's Inside (35 files)\n\n| Component | Count | Purpose |\n|-----------|-------|---------|\n| **Skills** | 26 | Step-by-step development guides |\n| **Agents** | 4 | Cross-cutting auditors (access control, migrations, plugins, pipeline) |\n| **Hooks** | 4 | Automated pre/post-tool safety checks |\n| **Config** | 2 | `settings.json` (hook wiring) + `mcp.json` (7 MCP servers) |\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n**Skills** split into two categories:\n- Prescriptive `add-X` / `debug-X` skills with numbered steps, real file paths, and a Verify section\n- Reference `X-reference` skills documenting complex subsystems (DAG message history, PersistentConfig, plugin system)\n\n**Hooks** follow the stdin-JSON pattern: read tool input via `cat`, extract `file_path` with `python3 -c`, exit `2` to block or `0` to allow. The most important is `guard-protected-files.sh` which blocks edits to `.env`, existing migrations, and `.webui_secret_key`.\n\n**Agents** output structured `PASS/FAIL/WARNING` checklists rather than prose — appropriate for audits of access control, migration safety, and plugin structure.\n\n### Critical Gotchas Captured\n- `outlet()` filter hook doesn't run for `/v1/chat/completions` API clients\n- Filter plugins **must** have `Valves` with a `priority: int` field\n- Manifold ID parsing splits on **first** dot, not last\n- `except HTTPException: raise` must come **before** `except Exception` in router handlers\n- Message history is a DAG — always use `buildMessages()`, never iterate `history.messages` directly","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7409b3d0-b8af-4d93-ba37-d08dbbd0776c","total_cost_usd":0.3982402,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":28716,"cache_read_input_tokens":74388,"output_tokens":7448,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":28716,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":533,"cache_read_input_tokens":34730,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6048,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6048},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":7448,"cacheReadInputTokens":74388,"cacheCreationInputTokens":28716,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.24174239999999997,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":70,"outputTokens":9035,"cacheReadInputTokens":461203,"cacheCreationInputTokens":52106,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.15649780000000002,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"module_path":"test-repos/","purpose":"A fully generated .claude/ configuration for open-webui (a self-hosted AI chat platform), produced by ultrainit as a reference output. It serves dual purposes: a real-world example of what ultrainit generates, and a fixture for integration validation of the ultrainit pipeline.","architecture":{"overview":"The directory contains a complete Claude Code configuration organized into five component types: 26 skills (task-specific step-by-step guides), 4 agents (cross-cutting auditors), 4 hooks (automated pre/post-tool safety checks), and 2 config files (settings.json for hook wiring, mcp.json for external tool servers). There is no application code — only markdown and bash files that encode the open-webui project's conventions, patterns, and gotchas for Claude Code consumption.","subdirectories":[{"path":"test-repos/.claude/skills/","purpose":"26 Markdown skill files covering every open-webui development workflow — feature addition, debugging, database migrations, plugin authoring, release workflow, and pre-PR checks. Each skill is a prescriptive step-by-step guide with YAML frontmatter, code examples referencing real file paths, and a verification section.","key_files":["add-router-endpoint.md","add-entity-model.md","add-svelte-component.md","add-plugin.md","add-db-migration.md","debug-chat-pipeline.md","access-control-reference.md","persistent-config-reference.md","pre-pr-checklist.md","plugin-authoring-reference.md"]},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/agents/","purpose":"4 specialized auditor agents that Claude Code can invoke for complex cross-cutting analysis: access control verification, full chat pipeline tracing, migration safety review, and plugin structure validation. Each outputs structured PASS/FAIL/WARNING checklists rather than prose.","key_files":["access-control-auditor.md","chat-pipeline-analyzer.md","migration-safety-reviewer.md","plugin-structure-validator.md"]},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/hooks/","purpose":"4 bash hook scripts wired into settings.json. Two auto-format (ruff for Python, prettier for frontend), one blocks edits to protected files (credentials, migration versions, secret keys), and one reminds about i18n:parse on session exit.","key_files":["guard-protected-files.sh","autoformat-python.sh","autoformat-frontend.sh","i18n-reminder.sh"]},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/","purpose":"Root config files: settings.json wires all four hooks to their trigger events (PreToolUse/Edit, PostToolUse/Edit, PostToolUse/Write, Stop). mcp.json configures 7 MCP servers (svelte, context7, playwright, postgres, sqlite, docker, python-tools).","key_files":["settings.json","mcp.json"]}],"data_flow":"When a developer uses Claude Code on open-webui: (1) PreToolUse/Edit fires guard-protected-files.sh — reads JSON from stdin, extracts file_path, blocks or warns. (2) Developer invokes a skill by name (e.g. 'add-router-endpoint') — Claude reads the skill markdown and follows its numbered steps. (3) PostToolUse/Edit fires autoformat-python.sh for .py files in /backend/; PostToolUse/Write fires autoformat-frontend.sh for .ts/.svelte/.js/.css/.json in /src/ or /cypress/. (4) For complex audits, Claude invokes an agent (e.g. 'access-control-auditor') which runs a structured checklist. (5) On Stop, i18n-reminder.sh checks for modified Svelte/TS files containing i18n calls and reminds the developer to run i18n:parse."},"key_files":[{"path":"test-repos/.claude/skills/add-router-endpoint.md","purpose":"Canonical skill for adding CRUD endpoints to FastAPI routers. Establishes URL shape conventions (GET /list, POST /create, GET /id/{id}, POST /id/{id}/update, DELETE /id/{id}/delete) and the full auth + error handling pattern. Most referenced pattern in the project.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/skills/add-entity-model.md","purpose":"Defines the five-section entity model pattern: SQLAlchemy ORM class, Pydantic DTO, Forms/Responses, Repository class (ThingsTable), and module-level singleton. This pattern is used by every backend model in open-webui.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/skills/add-plugin.md","purpose":"Covers all four plugin types (Pipe/Filter/Action/Manifold) with Valves, UserValves, dunder parameters, and the required priority field for filters. Includes the Manifold ID parsing gotcha (split on first dot only).","importance":"critical"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/hooks/guard-protected-files.sh","purpose":"PreToolUse hook that blocks edits to .env files, .webui_secret_key, existing Alembic migrations, and existing Peewee legacy migrations. Warns (non-fatal) on security-critical source files. The most important safety mechanism in the config.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/agents/access-control-auditor.md","purpose":"Structured auditor that verifies the three-layer access control model (feature gate → admin bypass → per-resource grant), checks for N+1 anti-patterns in list endpoints, and validates write protection filters on access_grants input.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/agents/migration-safety-reviewer.md","purpose":"Pre-apply migration validator covering SQLite compatibility (batch_alter_table requirement), idempotency guards, column conventions, data migration safety, and downgrade() correctness. Outputs PASS/FAIL/WARNING per checklist item.","importance":"important"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/skills/debug-chat-pipeline.md","purpose":"Traces the full request flow through open-webui's 6500-line middleware.py for all chat modes (plain, RAG, tool-enabled, Pipe function). Identifies silent failure points in the pipeline.","importance":"important"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/skills/access-control-reference.md","purpose":"Reference skill documenting the three-layer permission model, BYPASS_ADMIN_ACCESS_CONTROL behavior, feature gate syntax, and AccessGrants batch API.","importance":"important"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/settings.json","purpose":"Hook wiring: maps PreToolUse/Edit → guard-protected-files.sh, PostToolUse/Edit → autoformat-python.sh, PostToolUse/Write → autoformat-frontend.sh, Stop → i18n-reminder.sh.","importance":"important"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/mcp.json","purpose":"Configures 7 MCP servers: svelte, context7, playwright, postgres (with connection string env var), sqlite, docker, python-tools.","importance":"reference"},{"path":"test-repos/.claude/skills/pre-pr-checklist.md","purpose":"Lists all CI gates that will fail silently if missed: ruff format, i18n:parse + diff check, alembic heads --check, svelte-check. Critical for shipping without CI surprises.","importance":"reference"}],"patterns":[{"name":"YAML Frontmatter Skill Declaration","description":"Every skill file starts with YAML frontmatter containing `name` (kebab-case) and `description`. The description MUST include trigger phrases ('Use when asked to...') and negative scope ('Do NOT use for...'). This is enforced by validate-skill.sh in the ultrainit pipeline.","example_files":["test-repos/.claude/skills/add-router-endpoint.md","test-repos/.claude/skills/add-svelte-component.md","test-repos/.claude/skills/add-plugin.md"]},{"name":"Prescriptive Numbered Step Skills","description":"Skills are structured as: (1) Before You Start — files to read first, (2) Numbered implementation steps with exact code examples from real files, (3) Verify section with exact commands to run, (4) Common Mistakes section listing anti-patterns. Skills teach a pattern once then reference it; they don't repeat themselves.","example_files":["test-repos/.claude/skills/add-router-endpoint.md","test-repos/.claude/skills/add-entity-model.md","test-repos/.claude/skills/add-db-migration.md"]},{"name":"PASS/FAIL/WARNING Auditor Agents","description":"Agents are structured auditors that output structured checklists rather than prose. Each checklist item has a verdict (PASS/FAIL/WARNING) and corrected snippets for failures. Agents handle cross-cutting concerns too complex for a single skill (access control, migration safety, plugin validation).","example_files":["test-repos/.claude/agents/access-control-auditor.md","test-repos/.claude/agents/migration-safety-reviewer.md","test-repos/.claude/agents/plugin-structure-validator.md"]},{"name":"stdin-JSON Hook Pattern","description":"All hooks read tool input JSON from stdin via `input=$(cat)`, then extract the relevant field (file_path, tool_name, etc.) using python3 -c or jq. Exit code 2 blocks the tool; exit 0 allows it. Warnings are written to stderr. Hooks use `set -euo pipefail` and handle missing input gracefully (empty string defaults).","example_files":["test-repos/.claude/hooks/guard-protected-files.sh","test-repos/.claude/hooks/autoformat-python.sh","test-repos/.claude/hooks/i18n-reminder.sh"]},{"name":"Reference vs Prescriptive Skill Split","description":"Skills split into two types: (1) Prescriptive 'add-X' skills with step-by-step implementation guides, and (2) Reference 'X-reference' skills that document architecture, domain knowledge, or complex subsystems for reading. Reference skills are invoked when debugging or making architectural decisions; prescriptive skills are invoked when implementing.","example_files":["test-repos/.claude/skills/persistent-config-reference.md","test-repos/.claude/skills/access-control-reference.md","test-repos/.claude/skills/plugin-authoring-reference.md","test-repos/.claude/skills/message-history-dag-reference.md"]},{"name":"Real File Path Anchoring","description":"Every skill, agent, and the CLAUDE.md reference actual files in the open-webui codebase with exact paths (e.g., `backend/open_webui/models/users.py`, `src/lib/components/chat/Messages.svelte`). This is a validation requirement: skills must have minimum 3 real file references. Generic paths like `src/components/MyComponent.svelte` are rejected.","example_files":["test-repos/.claude/skills/add-router-endpoint.md","test-repos/.claude/skills/debug-rag-retrieval.md","test-repos/.claude/agents/chat-pipeline-analyzer.md"]}],"conventions":{"naming":"Skills: kebab-case filenames matching frontmatter `name` field (add-router-endpoint.md). Agents: kebab-case with descriptive suffix (access-control-auditor.md, migration-safety-reviewer.md). Hooks: verb-noun kebab-case (guard-protected-files.sh, autoformat-python.sh). Two skill categories by prefix: `add-` for prescriptive guides, `debug-` for debugging guides, `X-reference` for reference docs.","imports":"No imports — all files are self-contained markdown or bash. Hook scripts use only bash builtins, python3 -c for JSON parsing, and call external tools (ruff, npx) with silent failure if unavailable.","error_handling":"Hooks use exit code 2 to block tool execution (hard stop), exit 0 to allow. Warnings are written to stderr and shown to the user but don't block. Auto-format hooks use `|| true` or check tool availability before running to avoid false-blocking on missing tools. All hooks use `set -euo pipefail`.","other":["Skill descriptions always include negative scope ('Do NOT use for...') to prevent misapplication — enforced by validate-skill.sh","Agent frontmatter includes tool scoping restrictions appropriate to the audit task","mcp.json uses env var placeholders (POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING) as comments rather than hardcoded credentials","settings.json uses matcher strings ('Edit', 'Write') not glob patterns for hook triggering","Skills avoid generic programming phrases ('best practice', 'clean code') — enforced by validate-skill.sh","Every prohibition in CLAUDE.md and skills includes an explicit alternative ('Don't do X, do Y instead')"]},"dependencies":{"internal":["ultrainit/scripts/validate-skill.sh — validates skill frontmatter and content quality","ultrainit/scripts/validate-subagent.sh — validates agent frontmatter and content quality","ultrainit/lib/merge.sh — writes artifacts to .claude/ with safe merge (never overwrite existing skills/agents/hooks)"],"external_key":[{"name":"ruff","purpose":"Auto-format Python files in autoformat-python.sh hook"},{"name":"npx + prettier","purpose":"Auto-format Svelte/TS/JS/CSS/JSON files in autoformat-frontend.sh hook"},{"name":"python3","purpose":"JSON parsing in hook scripts (extracts file_path from tool input)"},{"name":"@sveltejs/mcp","purpose":"MCP server for Svelte language tools"},{"name":"@upstash/context7-mcp","purpose":"MCP server for context management"},{"name":"@playwright/mcp","purpose":"MCP server for browser automation / E2E"},{"name":"@marcelo-ochoa/server-postgres","purpose":"MCP server for direct PostgreSQL access"},{"name":"mcp-sqlite-tools","purpose":"MCP server for SQLite inspection"},{"name":"@alisaitteke/docker-mcp","purpose":"MCP server for container management"},{"name":"@paretools/python","purpose":"MCP server for Python utilities"}]},"domain_terms":[{"term":"Pipe","meaning":"Plugin type that replaces or augments the LLM call — receives messages and returns a generator. The core extension point for custom model routing."},{"term":"Filter","meaning":"Plugin type with inlet() (pre-LLM) and outlet() (post-LLM) hooks. MUST have a Valves class with a priority: int field. outlet() does NOT run for /v1/chat/completions API clients."},{"term":"Action","meaning":"Plugin type that adds buttons to the chat UI for post-message actions."},{"term":"Manifold","meaning":"Plugin type that exposes multiple model IDs from one plugin. IDs are parsed by splitting on the FIRST dot only."},{"term":"Valves","meaning":"Admin-configurable settings nested class inside a plugin (Pydantic BaseModel). Persisted to DB, visible in admin UI."},{"term":"UserValves","meaning":"Per-user configurable settings nested class inside a plugin. Visible to end users in chat settings."},{"term":"Dunder parameters","meaning":"Double-underscore prefixed parameters injected by the pipeline at call time (__user__, __metadata__, __event_emitter__). Must be Optional with None defaults and STRIPPED from LLM-visible tool specs."},{"term":"PersistentConfig","meaning":"Generic wrapper class for admin settings. Reads from env var on first access, then persists overrides to DB. Supports hot reload without restart."},{"term":"RAG","meaning":"Retrieval-Augmented Generation — vector search over knowledge bases injected into chat context. Collection naming is implicit (derived from knowledge base ID), no error when collection missing."},{"term":"Arena model","meaning":"Anonymous A/B comparison mode where two models respond to the same prompt and users vote. Special routing in middleware.py."},{"term":"DAG message history","meaning":"Chat messages stored as a directed acyclic graph (JSON blob) to support branching conversations. Uses buildMessages() to linearize. currentId tracks the active branch head."},{"term":"BYPASS_ADMIN_ACCESS_CONTROL","meaning":"Config flag (defaults True) that makes admins bypass all per-resource access grants. This is intentional — admins see everything by default."},{"term":"Peewee migrations","meaning":"Legacy migration system (backend/open_webui/internal/migrations/). FROZEN — never modify existing files. New schema changes use Alembic only."},{"term":"AccessGrants","meaning":"Per-resource permission grants table. Checked at layer 3 of access control. Use batch get_accessible_resource_ids() for list endpoints to avoid N+1 queries."}],"gotchas":[{"issue":"outlet() filter hook does NOT run for /v1/chat/completions API clients","solution":"If post-processing must apply to API clients too, implement it in the Pipe plugin type instead of an outlet() filter."},{"issue":"Existing Alembic migration files must never be edited after deployment — they corrupt the DB upgrade path","solution":"Always generate a new migration with `alembic revision --autogenerate -m 'description'`. guard-protected-files.sh hook enforces this by blocking edits to existing migration files."},{"issue":"Manifold plugin ID parsing must split on FIRST dot only, not last","solution":"Use `model_id.split('.', 1)` not `model_id.rsplit('.', 1)`. The prefix before the first dot is the manifold ID."},{"issue":"Dunder parameters (__user__, __metadata__, __event_emitter__) must be stripped from LLM-visible tool specs","solution":"The pipeline strips them automatically only if they follow the Optional[...] = None signature convention. Always use Optional type hints with None defaults."},{"issue":"Filter plugins MUST have a Valves class with a priority: int field","solution":"Always include `class Valves(BaseModel): priority: int = Field(default=0)` even if the filter has no other configuration."},{"issue":"Message history is a DAG JSON blob — iterating history.messages directly gives unordered results","solution":"Always use buildMessages(history, history.currentId) to get the ordered list for the current branch."},{"issue":"Svelte store mutations don't trigger reactivity without reassignment","solution":"Use spread updates: `settings.update(s => ({ ...s, key: val }))`. For arrays: `items = [...items, newItem]` not `items.push(newItem)`."},{"issue":"i18n must use getContext('i18n') inside Svelte components, not a module import","solution":"Always write `const i18n = getContext('i18n')` inside the <script> block. Module-level imports break SSR context."},{"issue":"The HTTPException re-raise pattern is critical — bare except catches HTTPException and wraps it in a 500","solution":"Always add `except HTTPException: raise` BEFORE `except Exception as e:` in try/except blocks in router handlers."},{"issue":"BYPASS_ADMIN_ACCESS_CONTROL defaults to True — admins bypass all per-resource grants","solution":"This is intentional. Don't add per-resource checks that assume admins are restricted. Explicitly check admin status when you need to restrict admin access."},{"issue":"Hook scripts must handle missing tool input gracefully (stdin may be empty or malformed)","solution":"Use `|| echo ''` defaults when extracting fields: `file_path=$(echo \"$input\" | python3 -c \"...\" || echo '')`"},{"issue":"MCP server configs in mcp.json contain placeholder env vars (POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING) that must be set before use","solution":"Check mcp.json env var requirements and set them in shell profile or .env before starting Claude Code."}],"commands":[{"command":"ls test-repos/.claude/skills/ | wc -l","purpose":"Count generated skills (should be 26 for open-webui reference)"},{"command":"ls test-repos/.claude/agents/","purpose":"List generated agents"},{"command":"bash ultrainit/scripts/validate-skill.sh test-repos/.claude/skills/add-router-endpoint.md","purpose":"Validate a skill file against ultrainit quality rules"},{"command":"bash ultrainit/scripts/validate-subagent.sh test-repos/.claude/agents/access-control-auditor.md","purpose":"Validate an agent file against ultrainit quality rules"},{"command":"grep -r 'Do NOT use for' test-repos/.claude/skills/ | wc -l","purpose":"Verify all skills have negative scope in their descriptions"},{"command":"cat test-repos/.claude/settings.json | jq '.hooks | keys'","purpose":"Inspect which hook event types are configured"}],"skill_opportunities":[{"name":"add-skill-file","description":"Guide for writing a new Claude Code skill for a target project — structuring frontmatter, prescriptive steps, real file references, and verification sections to pass validate-skill.sh","workflow_steps":["Identify the development workflow to cover (feature addition, debugging, or reference)","Choose skill type: prescriptive add-X, debug-X, or X-reference","Write YAML frontmatter with kebab-case name, trigger phrases, and negative scope","Structure body: Before You Start → numbered steps with code examples → Verify section → Common Mistakes","Anchor all examples to 3+ real file paths in the target codebase","Run validate-skill.sh to check quality gates"]},{"name":"add-hook","description":"Guide for writing a new Claude Code hook script for a project — stdin-JSON pattern, exit codes, and wiring into settings.json","workflow_steps":["Identify the trigger event (PreToolUse/Edit, PostToolUse/Write, Stop)","Write bash script with set -euo pipefail header","Read tool input from stdin via input=$(cat)","Extract relevant field (file_path, tool_name) with python3 -c or jq","Implement check logic with exit 2 for block, stderr for warning, exit 0 for allow","Add entry to settings.json hooks section with correct matcher"]},{"name":"validate-claude-config","description":"Run all ultrainit validation scripts against a generated .claude/ directory to check skill, agent, and hook quality before using as integration reference","workflow_steps":["Run validate-skill.sh on all files in .claude/skills/","Run validate-subagent.sh on all files in .claude/agents/","Check hooks have set -euo pipefail and read from stdin","Verify settings.json hook matchers reference existing hook scripts","Check CLAUDE.md length, generic phrase count, and prohibition alternatives","Report PASS/FAIL summary per artifact"]}]},"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a2704997-fe62-4663-bcd0-183d46f6bd9f"}
